department 
normally he said administrative law judges tell reporters 
seeking interviews to call an official spokesman of the federal 
agency where the judge works 
court judges rarely speak publicly about pending cases 
administrative law judges who interpret federal law and 
regulations enforced by the agencies for which they work are 
generally expected to follow the same standards as other judges 
