<TEXT>
soldiers mutinied across the northern 
coast of the countrys secondlargest island thursday in what 
appeared the first stage of a new attempt to overthrow president 
corazon aquino 
the mutineers on mindanao about 500 miles south of manila 
seized the city of butuan and also appeared to be in control of 
cagayan de oro a major port of about 200000 people 
they were led by the former chief of staff of mrs aquinos 
guard force who has been at large since participating in a bloody 
december coup attempt 
witnesses said rebels were marching around the streets of 
cagayan de oro in a virtual victory parade attracting large 
crowds of curiosity seekers 
the armed forces went on nationwide alert and mrs aquino 
gathered with her cabinet senior military officers and congressmen 
at the presidential palace 
im calling once again on the people to rally against these 
troublemakers mrs aquino said on the radio the constitution 
will be upheld with force when challenged with force 
military chief of staff gen renato de villa said the mutiny 
appeared a secessionist move and vowed to do whatever is 
necessary to prevent any dismemberment of this republic 
officials said about 200 rebels launched the revolt about 1 
am seizing the 402nd brigade army base in butuan about 500 
miles south of manila flights to mindanao were canceled and 
schools on the island closed 
the rebels later moved into cagayan de oro 70 miles west of 
butuan 
manila radio station dzxl interviewed their leader renegade 
col alexander noble at the regional national police headquarters 
in cagayan de oro 
this shows that the free mindanao movement is not just 
propaganda noble told reporters at camp evangelista 
in the city of iligan just west of cagayan de oro loyalist 
troops secured government buildings and blocked roads to the nearby 
military camp after residents said a rebel helicopter had hovered 
overhead and urged troops to join the mutiny the residents said 
government planes chased the helicopter away 
national security adviser rafael ileto said that the rebels hope 
to establish a secessionist government on mindanao then move up 
north 
there have been rumors that a coup attempt was brewing in the 
region for nearly six months 
military sources said the mutineers were planning to stage 
pocket rebellions in remote areas of the country before 
striking in the capital 
mrs aquino has survived six coup attempts since she took office 
in february 1986 in the most recent attempt in december rebels 
seized manilas financial district in bloody fighting and nearly 
toppled the government more than 100 people were killed 
also thursday a bomb exploded outside a manila army base three 
hours after the mindanao base was taken there were no injuries 
it was the 35th explosion in the capital since august officials 
see the bombings as the work of military officers hoping to 
destabilize the country 
de villa said soldiers from the 53rd infantry battalion one of 
the units at the 402nd brigade organized the takeover about 3000 
soldiers are based at the brigade 
