butuan and officials in manila were relying on commercial radio 
stations and the military regional headquarters in cagayan de oro 
de villa said he called commanding officers of various camps 
around the country and was assured of their loyalty 
i think this is small thing and we can control this de 
villa said in a radio interview we wish to inform the public 
that the armed forces is united except for this breakaway group 
we are in control of all units in manila and the entire country 
templo said there were no plans to send troops from luzon the 
main island to reinforce government forces on mindanao 
