<TEXT>
convicted bank robber dannie martin has broken 
the rules most of his life so hes not intimidated by prison 
regulations affecting his writing for the san francisco chronicle 
a recent court ruling upheld us bureau of prisons regulations 
that say a federal prisoner cant be paid for writing for a 
newspaper cant be given a byline and cant act as a reporter 
the ruling is being appealed and martin continues to write the 
features and commentary about prison life that have fascinated 
chronicle readers since 1986 
hes not getting paid and his stories dont carry a byline but 
he says he risks additional jail time if he is found to have acted 
as a reporter 
ive been an outlaw so long and saw myself that way ive 
usually been against what rules they had anyway so that doesnt 
bother me as much as it would a square said martin a former 
drug abuser who has spent 25 of his 51 years in prison 
