phoenix martin and the chronicle then filed suit to challenge the 
rules the bureau of prisons said he violated 
us district judge charles legge ruled in june that the 
regulations were justified by the bureaus authority over prison 
security he said outside newspaper reporting by inmates could 
cause rifts within a prison and improperly focus attention on 
individual inmates 
dan dunne a spokesman for the bureau of prisons said the rules 
were made for security reasons long before martin started writing 
for the chronicle 
