the lowest of the indian social system the untouchables and the 
tribespeople 
untouchables are below the four major castes which determine 
social position by birth and often sets economic and educational 
paths 
the decision touched off widespread riots across northern india 
killing at least 53 people and prompting curfews in more than a 
dozen areas at least 26 young people have committed suicide by 
burning themselves or eating poison 
whitecollar civil service jobs are coveted by many graduates 
the government employs about 18 million people 
many uppercaste students say they will be bypassed for jobs in 
favor of unqualifid candidates at present there are about 17 
million educated but unemployed youths in the nation of 800 million 
people 
in the lok sabha singh said he was deeply anguished by the 
suicides and hoped the students will accept his offer for talks 
several student groups have refused to open negotiations until the 
job policy is withdrawn 
india which is 82 percent hindu professes secularism and 
outlaws discrimination by caste but the practice persists 
singh has said the government plans to generate 3 million more 
jobs and is ready to give loans to youths who want to start 
businesses 
</TEXT>
