<TEXT>
standup tragedy is music video theater a 
contemporary kaleidoscope of story song and dance about the 
futility of teaching in an innercity high school 
if that sounds depressing well it is and it isnt the play 
which opened thursday at broadways criterion center theater is 
fast furious often funny and startlingly different call it a 
raw raucous updated blackboard jungle with a rap beat but 
with no easy answers and a pessimistic ending 
the story comes from author bill cains reallife experiences 
teaching in a catholic school on manhattans lower east side tom 
griffin played by jack coleman is an idealistic new teacher from 
a wealthy wasp family hes trying to save a little bit of the 
world and until now his only problem has been deciding on whether 
or not to go to law school 
instead he finds himself battling to teach young hispanics 
particularly a withdrawn student named lee marcus chong who has a 
problem home life lee an accomplished artist also has an 
overactive imagination the youth has created a fantasy world of 
comicstrip superheroes an exotic environment where he can block 
out his junkie of an older brother and his alcoholic mother 
tom tries to get through to lee but the more he tries to help 
the more it hurts lee your familys your fate says the 
fatalistic student and playwright cain poohpoohs the quickfix 
solution of education lifting these teenagers out of a life of 
poverty and crime his spokesman is a craggy nearly disillusioned 
cleric father ed larkin played with a fine sandpaper edge by 
charles cioffi 
larkin explains that an ecology of evil permeates the 
neighborhood and once you upset the balance who knows what will 
happen this environment is portrayed at warp speed by director ron 
link who never lets standup tragedy stop 
one scene blends quickly into the next the dialogue and music 
often machinegunning the actors all over the stage and some of 
the performers play more than one role often at the same time the 
babyfaced chong does triple duty in an unnerving series of 
transformations he changes from the bewildered lee to his defiant 
brother to the boys haughty mother its an amazing performance 
coleman exudes the right amount of whitebread benevolence as 
the dogood teacher and there are distinctive portraits drawn by 
john c cooke and dan gerrity as his cynical cohorts in the 
teaching profession 
four other students rap and jive their way through the 
production under the rapidfire choreography of charles 
randolphwright they are all over designer yael pardess grim 
graffitiscarred set with four high school lockers placed at stage 
center 
standup tragedy is unlikely broadway fare its 
unconventional and almost aggressive in its determination to turn 
the norms of straightforward plot and character upsidedown and 
insideout but stay with it its a wild and most satisfying ride 
