<TEXT>
the swedish army wishes the gripen 
combat plane were as imaginary as the mythological birdbeast whose 
name it bears 
army officers competing with the air force for dwindling 
military funds in a neutral nation call the singleseat gripen the 
greatest threat to defense since swedens last war with napoleon 
ended in 1814 
the griffin which had the head and wings of an eagle on a 
lions body symbolized strength and vigilance the supersonic 
gripen way behind schedule is more than 1 billion over budget 
and the first prototype crashed 
sweden a neighbor of the soviet union with only 84 million 
citizens says it needs a strong defense to reinforce its 
neutrality it has a conscript army of 750000 and produces most of 
its own weapons including missiles tanks submarines artillery 
and explosives 
inflation has reduced the value of military budgets for two 
decades and some experts fear the gripens rising costs will force 
sweden to compromise security for lack of money 
gen bengt gustafsson supreme military commander told 
parliament last month the military budget of 46 billion must be 
increased or sweden will have to revise its defense plans close 
bases reduce military service and dismantle the defense industry 
he also says however that the computerized jet is essential 
it can be programmed for aerial interception ground attack or 
reconnaissance in sweden which has long borders and is surrounded 
by water the air force would hold off an enemy until the army 
could mobilize 
the gripen is a about 45 feet long with a takeoff weight of 
eight tons half the size of the viggen warplane sweden has used 
for 15 years and is much more maneuverable 
army commander ake sagren anticipating a budget battle 
launched a public attack on the gripen in august the army risks 
being phased out the general wrote in the newspaper svenska 
dagbladet and sweden will have an excellent air force well into 
the next century without the new plane 
at a tank training center in kristianstad the southern regional 
capital col roland appelqvists face turned grim when the gripen 
was mentioned and said his base was targeted for closure 
if the aircraft project had stayed within its budget there 
would have been money for the base he said 
sweden budgeted the gripen its largest industrial project at 
866 billion when work began in 1982 but cost overruns total 
116 billion so far and it is 18 months behind schedule the 
second prototype has made several test flights but the first 
crashed after six flights 
the air force has ordered 30 planes and is expected to increase 
that to 140 by the end of the year money for the aircraft has been 
allocated in the longterm defense plan but the cost probably will 
rise to at least 80 million each from the original 65 million 
no outsiders are participating in the gripen project israel was 
building a similar plane the lavi a few years ago but gave up 
after the united states withdrew its backing because of mounting 
costs 
some of swedens largest companies are involved with the gripen 
including saab the ericsson telecommunications group and volvo 
aircraft engines 
saab officials say the civilian aircraft industry they have 
nurtured for a decade would die without the experience and spinoffs 
provided by the warplane gripen project 
parliament must decide by next year how to allocate defense 
money through 1996 gustafsson the supreme commander says 
increasing costs have had the effect over 20 years of nearly 
halving the number of operational defense units 
he said the military needs a grant of 410 million and annual 3 
percent budget increases through the 1990s to finance the gripen 
and current defense policies 
it is unlikely parliament will grant his request at a time when 
the soviet union perceived as the main threat to sweden is 
reducing military spending 
