on the sly under the threat of dismissal and they lapsed into 
addictive behaviors 
family and friends smuggled in tobacco 
people drove up to the center at odd hours dropped off 
packages and sped away 
a black market developed in which a single cigarette sold for 
3 to 5 
nicotine products were hidden in toilets ceilings radios and 
even body cavities 
patients went awol to walk to the corner gas station to buy 
cigarettes they were sneaking out at night climbing out of 
windows capretto said 
