from the transecuadorian pipeline between 1972 and october 1989 
with an estimated loss of 168 million gallons of oil the council 
said the pipeline was then operated by texaco it said 
the exxon valdez oil tanker spilled about 108 million gallons 
of oil into prince william sound in alaska in march 1989 
