<TEXT>
when things started looking bleak for 
bloomingdales corporate parent last autumn a manhattan movie 
theater near the famous department store proclaimed on its marquee 
good luck bloomies 
now a photograph of that message hangs on the wall outside the 
seventh floor board room at the bloomingdales headquarters it 
reminds executives of the goodwill that has accompanied the 
retailer since it entered bankruptcy proceedings in january 
to customers nothing seems much different but changes lie 
ahead at bloomingdales and the other eight chains of us 
department stores entangled in bankruptcy litigation by the sins of 
their parent campeau corp 
although hurt by the current spending slump and sure to suffer 
if the looming recession bears down on the economy the retailers 
probably will pull through bankruptcy although not necessarily 
intact 
executives running campeaus us retail arms allied stores 
corp and federated department stores inc are so sure of a 
successful conclusion to bankruptcy reorganization that they are 
planning on it 
allen i questrom chairman and chief executive of allied and 
federated joined by james m zimmerman president and chief 
operating officer presented a longterm business plan this past 
week that assumes the retailers will emerge in 1991 
questrom told a new york news briefing the allied and federated 
case could be one of the more successful bankruptcy reorganizations 
ever in retailing 
i think its a testimony to the strength of our organizations 
that they have survived this he said 
history might judge questrom and his colleagues as overly 
optimistic 
in fairness to them they acknowledged there are legal 
complications to unravel before the retailers are ready to operate 
without constraints a tax conflict must be resolved with the 
internal revenue service and junk bondholders threatening to sue 
allied must be placated 
howard davidowitz chairman of davidowitz amp associates inc a 
new yorkbased retail consulting firm said presentation of the 
upbeat business plan marked a preliminary skirmish in what will be 
a long negotiating battle between the forces of federated and 
allied and their creditors who are collectively owed around 77 
billion 
the debt was heaped on the retailers when the canadian real 
estate developer campeau bought them in the 1980s 
the retailers are posturing now trying to persuade creditors 
how valuable their department stores are that way creditors might 
think they are getting a good deal if theyre offered stakes in 
allied and federated davidowitz said 
campeaus us holding company federated stores inc is 
developing a reorganization plan in it federated will make 
compensation offers to creditors the offers to the banks 
suppliers and holders of junk bonds likely will be far less than 
100 cents on the dollar possibly a combination of cash and 
interests in a reorganized company 
federated so far has obtained two extensions in the time in 
which it has the exclusive right to write its own plan last month 
a federal bankruptcy judge in cincinnati delayed the deadline to 
feb 28 from sept 12 
companies operating under chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy 
act almost always need longer exclusivity periods than judges 
initially allot 
allied and federated which together operate 250 stores in 27 
states and employ about 100000 people wanted the deadline pushed 
past christmas so they could tote up their take from the years 
biggest sales season before proposing how their holdings might be 
divvied up 
it might not make much difference though because the retail 
industrys holiday will be mediocre at best the allied and 
federated business plan for the years through 1996 expects 
recessionary conditions to prevail from now through next years 
third quarter 
the allied and federated chains with some exceptions have had 
unimpressive sales so far in 1990 revenue slipped to 311 billion 
in the first half of this year from 32 billion a year earlier 
monthly statements submitted to bankruptcy court show they continue 
to bleed money 
questrom and zimmerman stressed at the briefing that the 
reorganization plan would not propose selling entire divisions of 
allied or federated instead they will close individual stores 
that fail to produce enough cash 
after questrom was recruited to run the retailers while they 
reorganized the proposed sale of bloomingdales was scrapped 
apparently even the crown jewel in federateds collection couldnt 
attract high enough bids 
regardless outsiders doubt federated and allied can be 
preserved in their present forms whole chains could go their 
separate ways as pieces of the campeau empire are carved up to pay 
creditors claims 
tortuous negotiations are in store with creditors fighting for 
what they think they should get davidowitz said asset sales will 
be the answer as impatient creditors seek to get as much money as 
possible as soon as possible with todays weak economy creditors 
will be less willing to accept equity stakes and bet on getting 
better returns sometime in the future 
how else are they going to get cash without selling assets 
davidowitz said theyre going to have to have billions in cash 
theyre just going to have to sell divisions 
i think theyre definitely going to emerge from bankruptcy but 
youre not going to recognize them he said they will emerge 
four or five years from today as a much smaller company even the 
divisions they keep will have fewer stores 
experts say average shoppers dont know and dont care that 
allied and federated are in a serious financial predicament 
bloomingdales has tried to preserve its pizazz and still 
conducts retailing as theater complete with splashy promotions and 
celebritystudded galas since last autumn the retailer has thrown 
about 10 chainwide events including one this september saluting 
spain and promoting spanish merchandise 
i dont see that the retail operations from a consumers 
point of view have any changes it seems to me to be business as 
usual said diann valentini who shops with an extra critical eye 
because of her job at the fashion institute of technology in new 
york 
valentini assistant chairwoman of fits fashion 
buyingmerchandising department said popular suppliers still are 
prominent at bloomingdales the chain continues to carry trendy 
merchandise and has been able to ride the crest of fashion waves 
its difficult to endure the scrutiny of a bankruptcy court 
judge and creditors but allied and federated have handled it well 
said lewis s rosenbloom an attorney with the chicago law firm 
winston amp strawn 
rosenbloom who represents unsecured creditors in the federated 
case said the situation is unusual for a retailing bankruptcy 
because the problems that drove the department stores into 
bankruptcy werent related to merchandising 
the retailers have benefitted from the goodwill of suppliers and 
financial backers 
in my experience what we have seen thus far in terms of the 
level of support is quite extraordinary rosenbloom said the 
vendor support has been substantial 
