assets of the nations 522 money market mutual 
funds rose 8654 million in the latest week to a new record of 
40996 billion the investment company institute said thursday 
the rise in the sevenday period ended wednesday broke the 
previous record of 40909 million set a week earlier that figure 
originally was reported as 40912 million but was revised by the 
washingtonbased mutual fund trade group 
in the latest week it said assets of 255 general purpose funds 
rose 1929 million to 14574 billion assets of 105 brokerdealer 
funds increased 856 million to 1659 billion and assets of 162 
institutional funds rose 5869 million to 9903 billion 
the sevenday average yield on money market mutual funds rose in 
the week ended tuesday to 748 percent from 747 percent the 
previous week said donoghues money fund report a trade journal 
in holliston mass 
the 30day average yield remained steady at 747 percent 
donoghues said 
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 
47 days up from 46 days donoghues said 
the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 100 leading 
commercial banks savings and loan associations and savings banks 
in the nations 10 largest markets showed the effective annual 
yield available on money market accounts was 605 percent as of 
wednesday the same as a week earlier 
the north palm beach flabased newsletter said the effective 
annual yield available on special savings accounts called super 
now accounts remained steady at 502 percent 
