tool and appliance giant black amp decker will 
sell four divisions for 150 million in order to meet payments on 
nearly 4 billion in debt taken on when it bought emhart corp 
the company agreed to sell its true temper hardware division to 
huffy corp of dayton ohio for about 55 million huffy said 
thursday 
in addition black amp decker is selling its medic division the 
medical computer system unit of planning research corp to a 
managementled buyout group and its domestic capacitors operation 
to an investment group yosemite investment inc 
the company announced wednesday it had agreed to sell 
gardenamerica which makes watering devices for lawns for 40 
million to james hardie industries ltd of australia 
the total sale price of all four divisions is expected to be 
about 150 million said the towson mdbased company 
we are pleased to announce another step in our program to 
reduce our acquisition debt by 1 billion black amp decker chief 
executive officer nolan archibald said when the proceeds of 
these sales are applied reductions will total approximately 700 
million 
black amp decker bought emhart corp last year with 38 billion 
in borrowed money since then the slumping economy has cut into 
sales leaving it strapped to make debt payments emhart is a 
farmington conn maker of industrial and consumer products 
clifford ransom an analyst with ferris baker watts in 
baltimore said the move is good news for black amp decker stock 
which has taken a beating 
people have been concerned over delays in selling assets 
ransom said this set of announcements indicates that program was 
only delayed not derailed so its good news 
black amp decker stock which had traded as high as 24 in the 
last year closed down another 75 cents to 887 thursday after 
falling 1 the previous day 
black amp decker was required to sell about 150 million in assets 
by the end of the year as part of its bank loan agreement ransom 
said 
the valuations theyre getting for these businesses look good 
although the details have been sketchy ransom said 
gardenamerica looks like it was bought at 13 times operating 
income which is good true temper looks like its between eight or 
nine times operating income i would guess thats a pretty good 
price 
the company also announced it had signed contracts to sell 
certain properties in the united kingdom and france 
