<TEXT>
the united steelworkers union is focusing on 
getting back wage concessions its members made in the early 1980s 
as the union prepares for the start of talks with usx corp 
the union will ask usx to raise pay 125 an hour andrew 
lefty palm district 15 director and chairman of the usx 
negotiating committee said thursday 
union members at usx make an average of 1084 an hour 
excluding benefits usw officials said 
the usw representing 18000 members at usx mines and mills in 
seven states opens talks with the nations largest steelmaker oct 
15 a fouryear contract expires feb 1 
were only asking to go back to what we made in 1982 palm 
said at a news conference at a hilton hotel in suburban moon 
township 
bethlehem steel corp national steel corp armco inc and two 
financially ailing steelmakers wheelingpittsburgh steel corp and 
ltv steel co all agreed to reinstate pay concessions palm said 
the key word gang is pattern plus he said the pattern 
is out there and they know what it is all the companies that 
signed up to the pattern still are making money 
usx chairman charles a corry and thomas j usher president of 
usxs steel division have said the company will stand alone in the 
talks ignoring agreements struck with competitors 
statements from both the union and usx said negotiations were 
scheduled to end nov 10 
the talks are beginning 3 months before the contracts 
expiration 1 months earlier than in previous years the usx 
statement did not explain the additional time but palm speculated 
the company was pressured by its customers into settling the 
contract early 
palm said the union will ask usx to pay a penalty into an 
industry fund for retraining workers if the company schedules 
excessive overtime the other steelmakers have accepted the 
penalty he said 
union leaders began two days of talks thursday with presidents 
and other officials of locals at usx operations the officials will 
return to the plants for two weeks of ironing out local issues 
before returning oct 29 for the companywide contract 
